race.comment: MARGIN CALL (2) won a Randwick trial and followed with an easy Maiden win at Canberra on debut. He stepped out in a CL1 at Hawkesbury 18 days later, beaten 1L when well supported. Draws awkwardly, but the gun jockey has been booked to ride the Maher-trained galloper and fitter again, he can bounce back. SHENANDOAH RIVER (8) is a threat. Raced a firm favourite and led and demolished the Maidens here by 3L first up and has been briefly freshened off that. He can control the race from the inside barrier and is sure to take stopping. SHE'S A BAD GIRL (10) didn't do a great deal when resuming over 1000m at Muswellbrook last start. Fitter and can only be improved. LILY BOBTAIL (9) rolled forward last time and boxed on to finish a nose from the winner at Taree, can give a sight again.
